1
00:00:43,720 --> 00:00:44,520
What's wrong?

2
00:00:45,080 --> 00:00:45,640
Nothing.

3
00:00:46,160 --> 00:00:47,020
An old problem.

4
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:02,960
Why are we here?

5
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:05,600
Let's rest here for a while before leaving.

6
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:08,160
I'm fine.

7
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:09,720
I just need a moment.

8
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:10,980
We still have time.

9
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:13,480
You are not in good condition,

10
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:15,120
so it's not suitable to travel.

11
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:17,440
We were just chased because we stayed at a hotel.

12
00:01:17,440 --> 00:01:19,200
I called the previous hotel.

13
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:23,130
It was because of the identity information we left at the front desk

14
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:24,260
that we were found.

15
00:01:24,960 --> 00:01:26,360
It should be safer here.

16
00:01:34,759 --> 00:01:35,320
Wait a minute.

17
00:01:35,320 --> 00:01:36,650
I need to get something.

18
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:04,040
Remarriage is impossible.

19
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,120
You did such a thing,

20
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:06,960
so don't even think about the child.

21
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:08,160
Of course, if you miss the child,

22
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:08,919
you can come and see.

23
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:10,720
Okay, that's it. Hanging up now.

24
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:13,120
Do you have any rooms?

25
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:14,640
Yes, please provide your ID.

26
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:15,480
It's not very convenient.

27
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:16,040
Then there's nothing I can do.

28
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:16,840
It's the rule.

29
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:24,730
Alright.

30
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:54,920
Hello. Is this the front desk?

31
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:56,120
Hello. What can I do for you?

32
00:02:56,120 --> 00:02:58,320
The air conditioner in my room is broken.

33
00:02:58,320 --> 00:02:59,720
There's no air coming out.

34
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:00,880
We can't fix that.

35
00:03:03,320 --> 00:03:04,840
Can I change rooms then?

36
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:05,800
Sir,

37
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:07,720
with the price and environment of our place,

38
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:09,760
the air conditioners in all rooms are the same.

39
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:12,240
Besides, do you two really need an air conditioner?

40
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:13,320
It'll get hot soon enough.

41
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:15,380
You might even need the cold air then.

42
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:36,440
Hello. Can I get an extra blanket?

43
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:38,400
We don't have any extra blankets.

44
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:39,720
Do you at least have hot water?

45
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:40,520
So demanding.

46
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:41,960
Here.

47
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:43,920
Thanks.

48
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,130
Have some hot water.

49
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:56,010
The temperature is just right.

50
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:24,560
ID card.

51
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:51,760
A veteran like you shouldn't sleep so soundly.

52
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:53,240
What?

53
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,080
Did a woman make you drop your guard?

54
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,820
Fell short of success.

55
00:05:58,640 --> 00:06:00,900
I didn't expect you to track me down here.

56
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,130
But you were wrong just now.

57
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:06,000
It wasn't a woman that made me relax.

58
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:06,800
It was money.

59
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:08,200
Money?

60
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:11,560
Someone offered me 1 million to protect her.

61
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:13,840
I thought I was going to succeed this time.

62
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:16,570
I had even figured out how to spend that 1 million.

63
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:17,600
What a pity.

64
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,200
I couldn't tell she was worth that much.

65
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:22,400
Yeah.

66
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:25,360
She looks pretty average.

67
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:28,160
But business is business.

68
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:30,760
We take people's money and fix their problems.

69
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:32,440
Since you tracked her down here,

70
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:34,240
she must be very important to you.

71
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:35,100
How about this?

72
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:37,200
Give me a million,

73
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,610
and you can take her.

74
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:41,400
You're selling me out just like that?

75
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:42,930
Aren't you a professional?

76
00:06:43,159 --> 00:06:44,600
You have no professional ethics.

77
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,860
Professional ethics?

78
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:46,800
Sister,

79
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:48,520
can't you see the situation?

80
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:49,600
The fact that I can stand here and talk means

81
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:51,730
he's already shown me enough respect.

82
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:53,280
Bro,

83
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,360
what do you think of my offer?

84
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:56,840
If you think it works,

85
00:06:56,840 --> 00:06:58,760
I'll turn around and leave right now.

86
00:06:58,760 --> 00:07:00,020
I don't have the money.

87
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:02,600
But I'm still taking her.

88
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:06,800
That's no way to do business.

89
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:09,280
You didn't even give me a chance to counteroffer.

90
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:10,140
How about this?

91
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:11,200
A flat rate.

92
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:12,980
Half a million.

93
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:15,320
I had a very traditional upbringing.

94
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:17,620
There are rules to follow in life.

95
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:20,480
My mission is to capture her,

96
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:22,680
not buy her.

97
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:27,890
Capture her?

98
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:31,760
Then why didn't you ambush us while we were asleep?

99
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:33,650
I told you, there are rules.

100
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:36,520
Ambushing people while they sleep

101
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:38,280
is a dirty trick.

102
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:40,090
I wouldn't stoop so low.

103
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:45,159
There are not many people like you these days.

104
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:46,640
But,

105
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:49,920
I'm sorry.

106
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:40,450
You go first.

107
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:41,840
Wait for me in the car.

108
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:36,840
Using a gun

109
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:38,840
is a bit against the rules, isn't it?

110
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:40,080
The gun is in my hand.

111
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:42,740
As long as you don't bother us,

112
00:09:43,560 --> 00:09:44,800
I can spare your life.

113
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:48,760
If I remember correctly,

114
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:51,520
you used to be a cop.

115
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:55,040
Can cops just shoot randomly?

116
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:56,360
You are right.

117
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,280
I used to be a cop.

118
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:02,160
So I'm even less likely to show mercy to criminals.

119
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:21,170
Pull over ahead.

120
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:50,360
Open the trunk.

121
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:00,640
What is this?

122
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:01,560
A tracker.

123
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:03,840
How did you know there was a tracker in the car?

124
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:05,440
Car rental companies are afraid of losing their cars,

125
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:07,360
so they usually install trackers.

126
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:10,160
He must have seen our car at the last hotel,

127
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:11,800
and found the rental company.

128
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:13,130
Are these the only ones?

129
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:15,140
This isn't a fancy car.

130
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:16,320
Three is plenty.

131
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:21,440
Wait a moment.

132
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:30,800
What's this?

133
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:33,260
Tinfoil. To block the signal.

134
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:40,000
Your wound.

135
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,520
It's nothing. Just a flesh wound.

136
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:42,050
Let's go.

137
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:54,320
What now?

138
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,560
Turn around and go back to town.

139
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:58,220
Your wound is still bleeding.

140
00:11:58,280 --> 00:11:59,610
We can't just ignore it.

141
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:04,080
That guy might still be in the city.

142
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:05,560
He might have even called for backup.

143
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:06,920
If you go back to the city now,

144
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:09,050
do you think I'm not hurt badly enough?

145
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:12,920
We are not far from the city.

146
00:12:12,920 --> 00:12:14,480
I'll hire a courier to buy some medicine.

147
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:16,610
They should be able to deliver it here.

148
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:23,120
This phone...

149
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:24,560
I hid this one earlier.

150
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:25,960
No one knows this number,

151
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,060
so they can't track it.

152
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:45,360
Does it end with 2350?

153
00:14:58,800 --> 00:14:59,680
Hello, it's me.

154
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:02,200
There's been a situation.

155
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:04,200
They should be heading to Yuanzhou.

156
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:05,400
I checked.

157
00:15:05,840 --> 00:15:08,680
There's an international train leaving at 3:00 p.m.

158
00:15:08,680 --> 00:15:10,480
Send someone to intercept them.

159
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:13,800
I don't have any connections at that train station.

160
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:15,000
That's your problem.

161
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:16,120
I'll tell you what.

162
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,960
I'll get some people to intercept them at the train station entrance.

163
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:20,360
But they won't arrive until 8:00 tomorrow.

164
00:15:42,520 --> 00:15:44,250
You all have the photos, right?

165
00:15:44,560 --> 00:15:45,680
You two take this entrance.

166
00:15:45,680 --> 00:15:46,810
We'll take that one.

167
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:53,500
We're done eating.

168
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:55,480
Are we going to the train station now?

169
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:57,800
We only took off the trackers in Songzhou.

170
00:15:57,800 --> 00:16:00,280
They probably know we're in Yuanzhou by now.

171
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:04,480
They should have people at the train station already.

172
00:16:04,520 --> 00:16:06,450
Besides, you're not feeling well.

173
00:16:06,640 --> 00:16:07,720
Let's rest for a bit.

174
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:08,200
No rush.

175
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:11,120
Sir.

176
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:13,610
What does this mean?

177
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:15,000
Take this

178
00:16:15,280 --> 00:16:16,410
to the address on it.

179
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:17,640
Remember.

180
00:16:17,640 --> 00:16:20,300
Don't open the foil until you are out of the city.

181
00:16:20,560 --> 00:16:22,160
I've never done this before.

182
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:24,480
Besides, this address is too far.

183
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:43,600
Hello.

184
00:16:44,080 --> 00:16:45,520
He is heading to Tangzhou.

185
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:48,920
Contact the people at the train station to follow the signal.

186
00:16:48,960 --> 00:16:50,520
Aren't you on that road?

187
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:54,440
I'll take a shortcut to intercept him and block both ends.

188
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:04,440
Okay.

189
00:17:05,240 --> 00:17:05,839
Got it.

190
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:07,280
Call them back.

191
00:17:07,280 --> 00:17:08,140
Let's retreat.

192
00:17:35,040 --> 00:17:36,240
Wait for me in the car.

193
00:17:36,440 --> 00:17:37,970
I'm going to buy something.

194
00:17:58,400 --> 00:18:00,160
Hello, do you have any hot drinks here?

195
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:01,020
Is coffee okay?

196
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:03,900
Yes, I'll take two.

197
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:04,370
Okay.

198
00:19:30,840 --> 00:19:30,920
Zhang Wei.
